Cell.Text: <<Shared>> You refer to the tomes of esoteric knowledge that old Hermaeus Mora has scattered throughout the world?
Do you know where I can find another Black Book?
Oh yes. They're not hard to locate once you know how to look for them. I have one here that I've been using to locate more.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroTopic: I hear you know where to find Black Books.

Cell.Text: [S] Found one? Yes, and you read it, too, didn't you? Don't try to deny it, you've got the look. I can see it now. | Dangerous knowledge is still knowledge and therefore useful. Usually turns out to be the most useful, in my experience.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroA1: I found a Black Book. I need to find more.

Cell.Text: Now that is a dangerous path indeed. Hermaeus Mora gives nothing away for free. | You may end up like Miraak, of course. Two power-mad Dragonborn. It could be very interesting.
Miraak? The one all the townsfolk are always chanting about?

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroB1: I have to know what Miraak knows if I want to stop him.

Cell.Text: Forbidden knowledge was somewhat of a specialty of the dwarves, eh? You don't think they would just leave it alone, do you?

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroD1: The Dwemer? What do they have to do with this?

Cell.Text: The book is housed in the main dome. I sealed the door the last time I was here, as a precaution against thieves and other meddlers.

Nchardak, an ancient Dwemer city, on the eastern side of Solstheim. It's largely flooded now, but luckily the main library is still above the water. | It seems the dwarves were as interested in the Black Books as we are. | They seem to have believed this one to be particularly valuable, as it is secured in a mechanism which I have been unable to open. Yet.

[S] G|It won't be easy. The whole lower part of the city is flooded, which has shut down the boilers which supply steam to the reading room. | If we can restore the steam supply, I'm certain I can open the book's protective case.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothGetBookTopic: How do we get the book out of its case?

Cell.Text: [S] Here are the cubes you left behind.
[S] Here, I picked up this cube for you.
S|You didn't know? Hmm, I thought it was obvious.
What do the Black Books have to do with Hermaeus Mora?

<<Shared>> Hermaeus Mora has always tried to seduce mortals into his service with the lure of forbidden knowledge. | Where the Black Books actually came from... no one really knows. Some appear to have been written far in the past, others might be from the future. | Apparently time is more malleable if you're the Daedric Prince of fate and destiny.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroHM: The Black Books have something to do with Hermaeus Mora?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Hermaeus Mora has always tried to seduce mortals into his service with the lure of forbidden knowledge. | Where the Black Books actually came from... no one really knows. Some appear to have been written far in the past, others might be from the future. | Apparently time is more malleable if you're the Daedric Prince of fate and destiny.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothBlackBooksTopic: What are these Black Books? Where do they come from?

Cell.Text: I'm afraid it isn't that simple. If it was, I would have the book already.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroD2: Just tell me where the book is and I'll go get it.

Cell.Text: [S] G|It seems the ancient Dwemer discovered this book and took it to study. | I found their "reading room" in the ruins of Nchardak. The book is there, but it's sealed in a protective case which I wasn't able to open. | But perhaps the two of us together will be able to get at the book. | To Nchardak, then. Follow me.

<<Shared>> If you have to ask that, you'd probably be best leaving his books to wiser heads than yours. | Like all Daedric Princes, he's not to be trifled with. But he is subtler than most of his ilk, appropriate for the prince of knowledge and fate. | Many scholars and loremasters have been ensared by the lure of learning the secrets that only Hermaeus Mora possesses. | But don't worry. I have no intention of joining them in their endless search through the infinite halls of Apocrypha.

I thought I made myself clear the first time. | The boilers in the Great Hall provide steam to the reading room upstairs, which we need in order to open the book's protective case. | We need a total of five cubes - one to operate the pumps in the Great Hall, the other four to activate the boilers.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothGetCubesTopic: Why do we need these cubes?

Cell.Text: I've dealt with Hermaeus Mora before. I've read the Oghma Infinium.

Have you? Then you know very well that he's not to be trifled with. | But he is subtler than most of the other Daedric Princes, as you would expect of the prince of knowledge and fate. | You seem to have escaped the fate of many who find themselves ensared forever by the lure of Hermaeus Mora's secrets. Or perhaps not.

<<Shared>> If you have to ask that, you'd probably be best leaving his books to wiser heads than yours. | Like all Daedric Princes, he's not to be trifled with. But he is subtler than most of his ilk, appropriate for the prince of knowledge and fate. | Many scholars and loremasters have been ensared by the lure of learning the secrets that only Hermaeus Mora possesses. | But don't worry. I have no intention of joining them in their endless search through the infinite halls of Apocrypha.
Is this somehow connected to your search for Miraak?
What could you know of them?

Well, I knew something connected with Hermaeus Mora was spreading its influence across the island. | I wasn't sure that it was in fact the same entity as this legendary namesake of the central temple. Although the villagers seem quite convinced.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroB2: Yes. You may have noticed he's trying to return to Solstheim.

Cell.Text: Yes. I haven't been idle while this fascinating madness engulfed Solstheim. | But my book isn't what you're looking for. I'm quite sure it is unconnected with this Miraak. | But I do know where to find a Black Book that can help you.

Oh, it clearly is not associated with the same power that has overtaken the island. | And I'm not talking about Hermaeus Mora. These Black Books are all his, of course. | No, what you're looking for is a specific book. Presumably because Miraak's power derives from it.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroC2: Why won't the book you have here help me?

Cell.Text: Yes, I do. I haven't been able to get it, though. But maybe together we can unlock the secrets the Dwemer left behind.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ04NelothIntroC3: So you know where to find this Black Book? The one connected with Miraak?
